title: tao_fa
body:
Tao Fa, also known as Great Sage Ratna (ラトナ大聖, Ratna Taisei), was a member of Lord Tensen, as well as one of the rulers of Kotaku. She maintains the female gender throughout the series. 

She has a very close relationship with [[Ju Fa]].

Like the rest of Lord Tensen, Tao Fa is named after a flower. "Tao Fa" (桃花) meaning "[[peach blossom]]". Furthermore, Tao Fa's hair is in the shape of the petals from the [[peach blossom]] flower.

title: jr_103_series
body:
The 103 series (103系, 103-kei) is a [[multiple unit train|DC electric multiple unit]] (EMU) commuter [[train]] type introduced in 1963 by [[Japan Railways|Japanese National Railways (JNR)]], and currently operated by [[West Japan Railway Company|West Japan Railway Company (JR West)]] and Kyushu Railway Company (JR Kyushu). They were also formerly operated by [[East Japan Railway Company|East Japan Railway Company (JR East)]], [[Central Japan Railway Company|Central Japan Railway Company (JR Central)]]. And [[Kereta Api Indonesia|KAIcommuter/CommuterLine]]

title: freedom_planet
body:
[b]Freedom Planet[/b] is a [[sonic_(series)|Sonic]]-inspired 2D platform video game franchise. There are 2 titles: [[Freedom Planet 1]] and [[Freedom Planet 2]]. Characters in FP2 have aged up and adopted very different visual designs.

In Freedom Planet 1, The player controls one of three [[furry|anthropomorphic animal]] protagonists: the dragon [[sash lilac_(fp1)|Lilac]], the wildcat [[carol tea_(fp1)|Carol]], or the basset hound [[milla basset_(fp1)|Milla]]. Aided by the duck-like [[commander_torque_(fp1)|Torque]], the player attempts to defeat [[arktivus brevon|Lord Brevon]], who plans to conquer the galaxy. While the game focuses on fast-paced platforming, its levels are interspersed with slower action scenes.

Freedom Planet 2 features 4 playable characters: [[Sash Lilac_(fp2)|]] the Water Dragon, [[Carol Tea_(fp2)|]] the Wildcat, [[Milla Basset_(fp2)|]] the Hound, and [[Neera Li_(fp2)|]] the Frost Knight Panda.

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Freedom Planet":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freedom_Planet]

title: 7-eleven
body:
An international chain of 24-hour [[convenience store]]s that originated and is still headquartered in Dallas, Texas, United States. Its stores are located in 20 countries (as of August 2024), Japan having one of its largest markets.

In 1991, Japanese affiliate Ito-Yokado acquired 70% of 7-Eleven and it was reorganized as a wholly owned subsidiary of 7-Eleven Japan. As of 2005, it is now held by the Japanese diversified retail group Seven & I Holdings Co., Ltd. (which also owns [[Denny's]] Japan).

title: kaidou_(one_piece)
body:
[[One Piece]] character, and the main antagonist of the Wano arc. He is the captain of the Beast Pirates, the tyrannical ruler of the Wano nation, and father of [[Yamato (one piece)|]].

Having consumed the Uo Uo no Mi, Model: Seiryu [[Devil Fruit]], which grants him a near-invincible body and incredible strength, as well as allows him to transform into a huge [[eastern dragon]]. Kaidou became so strong that he developed suicidal thoughts out of boredom and aimed to create a "World of Violence" so that he would eventually be killed in a "great battle".

title: nanaco_(mascot)
body:
The official [[giraffe]] mascot of the Nanaco electronic money service operated by Seven & i Holdings in Japan.

Introduced in 2007 to represent the e-money brand. The giraffe shape was chosen because its long neck resembles the numeral “7,” aligning with the “nana” (seven) in “Nanaco.” Her body features a pattern of seven colors, symbolizing the service’s 7-days-a-week convenience.

"Official character bio and lore.":[https://www.nanaco-net.jp/nanacofamily/]

title: bombergirl
body:

title: mary_janes
body:
A style of women's [[shoes]] characterized by a single strap across the top of the foot in place of laces or a zipper. Usually [[black footwear|black]], short-heeled or [[flats|flat]], and very smooth-featured, with a simple buckle to hold the strap tight. Commonly seen on [[school uniform]]s, [[lolita fashion]], and fetish porn stars.

Not to be confused with [[loafers]] which can also have a strap but running over a leather top. See the example post

Not to be confused with [[uwabaki]], which is the Japanese school indoor shoes.

h4. Examples

* !post #6381293
* !post #8440866

title: chin-chin
body:
A Japanese term with several different meanings. It can be onomatopoeia for the sound of a [[bird]] chirping (ちんちん chin-chin), a Japanese equivalent of the "beg" command for a [[dog]] (チンチン chin-chin), and it can also be used as a euphemism or slang for [[penis|male genitalia]] (ちんちん chin-chin or TNTN - short for "Tintin" - in Japanese-style romanization).

This phrase is commonly associated with [[Mystia Lorelei]] from the [[Touhou]] series, because she is a bird youkai.  For tagging purposes, this tag is only to be used when Mystia herself is saying the phrase, or when it's used to refer to her (as in post #510353).

title: arcana_heart
body:
A 2D arcade fighting game developed by Examu Inc. (formerly Yuki Enterprise) and distributed by [[Atlus]] to PlayStation 2 version. The game features an original all-female cast (each a variation of the moe archetype), and after choosing a character, the player chooses an "elemental alignment", or Arcana, which determines the character's special moves.

h4. Characters Introduced in Arcana Heart

* [[Aino Heart]] and her Love Arcana, Partinias.
* [[Daidouji Kira]] and her Water Arcana, Niptra.
* [[Fiona Mayfield]] and her Metal Arcana, Orichalkos.
* [[Kasuga Maori]] and her Earth Arcana, Ohtsuchi.
* [[Konoha (arcana_heart)|]] and her Nature Arcana, Moriomoto.
* [[Lieselotte Achenbach]] and her Shadow Arcana, Gier.
* [[Lilica Felchenerow]] and her Wind Arcana, Tempestas.
* [[Mei-Fang]] and her Fire Arcana, Lang-Gong.
* [[Mildred Avallone]], the final boss.
* [[Tokinomiya Kamui]] and her Time Arcana, Anutpada.
* [[Tsuzura Saki]] and her Lightning Arcana, Bhanri.
* [[Yasuzumi Yoriko]] with her demonic staff [[Mike (arcana_heart)|]] and her Death Arcana, Dieu Mort.

title: terapagos
body:
A Normal-type Legendary [[pokemon (creature)|Pokémon]], #1024 in the National Pokédex.

A [[turtle]]-like Pokémon with [[blue skin]], [[aqua eyes]], and a [[crystal]]line [[shell]]. Plays a major role in [[pokemon sv|Pokémon Scarlet and Violet]]'s Indigo Disk DLC, as well as in [[pokemon_horizons|Pokémon Horizons]]. [spoiler]It is the source of the [[Terastallization|Terastal]] phenomenon.[/spoiler]

It has three forms. When sent into battle, it changes from its [[terapagos (normal)|Normal Form]] to its larger [[terapagos (terastal)|Terastal Form]]. Upon Terastallizing, it changes into its [[terapagos (stellar)|Stellar Form]].

Japanese name: [b]Terapagos[/b]

h4. Official art

* !asset #25194045: [[terapagos (stellar)|Stellar Form]]

h4. See also:

title: obi-wan_kenobi_(disney+)
body:
Obi-Wan Kenobi is an American television miniseries created for the streaming service Disney+. It is part of the [[Star Wars]] franchise, beginning ten years after the events of [[star wars: revenge of the sith|Star Wars: Episode III – Revenge of the Sith]], and stars [[Ewan McGregor]] as the [[Obi-Wan Kenobi|title character]], reprising his role from the Star Wars prequel trilogy.
h4.Plot
After remaining in hiding for the next ten years on the planet [[Tatooine]], watching over [[anakin skywalker|Anakin's]] son [[Luke Skywalker|Luke]], Kenobi is called on a mission to rescue Anakin's daughter [[princess leia|Leia]] when she is kidnapped by the Galactic Empire's Jedi-hunting Inquisitors in a plot to draw Kenobi out. This brings Kenobi into conflict with [[darth vader|Vader]], who he believed to be dead, forcing Kenobi to face his traumatic past and guilty feelings.

title: kde
body:
[b]KDE[/b] is an international free software community that develops free and open-source software.

It is behind the creation and development of [[KDE Plasma]], its flagship desktop environment.

[[Krita (Software)]], a free and open source digital painting application, is also developed by KDE.

KDE's mascot is [[Konqi]], a cartoonish green dragon (re)designed by [[Tyson Tan]]. The female counterpart is [[Katie (KDE)]].

h4. See also

* [[Krita (Software)|]]

title: red_arrow_and_circle_(meme)
body:
[[Meme]] parodying clickbait [[YouTube]] thumbnails and other social media posts by including a red circle and an arrow pointing towards it in order to emphasize a usually already emphasized part of an image or point out the obvious.

Sometimes also used to imply whatever's in the circle and what's pointing to the circle are the same thing, such as in the case of name soundalikes, or to indicate that a character is responsible for an action.

title: undersized_clothes
body:
The opposite of [[oversized clothes]], this is for posts showing a situation wherein the clothes are obviously too small for the wearer. This can especially occur when two characters [[costume_switch|switch costumes]].

Undersized clothing are often caused by [[weight gain]]; many images depicting this include this tag.

title: sakamata_chloe
body:
A [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] from [[hololive]]'s 6th generation "[[holoX]]". Designed by [[Parsley-F]].

Her general activities ended on January 26th, 2025, but she did not fully "graduate" and is still affiliated with Cover Corp, participating in future projects.

While canonically an [[orca girl]], she does not have enough orca-like features to be tagged as such on Danbooru.

She has [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[grey hair]] with [[black hair|black]] [[streaked hair|streaks]], [[red eyes]] and [[large breasts]]. She also has [[multiple piercings|multiple]] [[spike piercing|spike]] and hoop [[ear piercing]] and an [[earclip]].

Her regular hairstyle with her default costume is [[wavy hair]] with [[double-parted bangs|double-parted]] [[center-flap bangs|center-flap]] [[braided bangs]], decorated with [[x hair ornament|crossing]] [[hairclip]]s. She also got an additional [[official alternate hairstyle]] for her default outfit consisting of [[long hair|long]] [[straight hair]] with sidelocks, a [[side braid]] and additional hairclips.

title: pennsylvania_(azur_lane)
body:
Azur Lane's personification of the American battleship USS [i]Pennsylvania[/i].

She has [[brown hair]] tied in a [[ponytail]], [[green eyes]] and a scar on her left cheek, likely referencing the minor damage she took at Pearl Harbor. Her attire consists of a partially unbuttoned blue [[military uniform]], revealing a black [[bikini top only|bikini top]], [[high heels]] and black [[pantyhose]]. A tiny sailor's hat rests on her head.

title: bust_chart
body:
A [[lineup]] of characters, usually in [[profile]], to compare their [[breasts|breast]] sizes.

The typical format of bust charts originated in 2004 with post #13199, a [[reference sheet]] for [[My-HiME]] published in [[Megami Magazine]].

Also referred to as 'chichikurabe' (lit. "breast comparison"). May or may not include actual numbered measurements.

title: heretics_(nikke)
body:
A "squad" from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]].

Traitor Nikkes who fight for the Raptures and their Queen, hybridized with Rapture technology and armor to serve as her agents. Throughout the Rapture Invasions, many Heretics form their own subfactions:

h5.Offspring
A group of Heretics with unknown goals. Named after various philosophies or ideologies.
* [[Nihilister (nikke)|]]
* [[Liberalio (nikke)|]]
* [[Indivilia (nikke)|]]

h5.Four Beasts
Four Heretics named after mythological creatures in the Bible. They are Heretics with different goals from their kin, however, the Four Beasts hold a grudge against the Offsprings for disregarding them.
* [[Behemoth (nikke)|]]
* [[Leviathan (nikke)|]]
* Bahamut
* Ziz

So far [[Modernia (nikke)|]] is the only Heretic that is not yet confirmed to be in any Heretic factions.
other_names: ヘレティック(勝利の女神:NIKKE)

title: krita_(software)
body:
Krita is a free and open-source raster graphics editor designed primarily for digital painting and 2D animation. It features an OpenGL-accelerated canvas, colour management support, an advanced brush engine, non-destructive layers and masks, group-based layer management, vector artwork support and switchable customisation profiles. It is written in C++ using Qt and runs on Windows and Unix-like operative systems.

Krita is developed by [[KDE]].

Krita's mascot is [[Kiki the Cyber Squirrel]] designed by [[Tyson Tan]].

h4. External links
https://krita.org/

title: lenna
body:
[b]Lenna[/b] (or [b]Lena[/b]) is a standard test image used in the field of digital image processing, starting in 1973. It is a picture of the Swedish model Lena Forsén, shot by photographer Dwight Hooker and cropped from the centerfold of the November 1972 issue of Playboy magazine.

title: wilson_gerecke_(ethan_forsythe)
body: Original character from [[Ethan Forsythe]]'s series "Akagi²":[/pools/15941]. Hailing from the Eagle Union, he is the base's current chaplain, attending to the religious needs of the base personnel, much to the disapproval from some (e.g. the Iris Libre). He is loosely based on the real-life Henry F. Gerecke, the Protestant chaplain who served at Nuremberg during the Nuremberg Trials. (The historical Chaplain Gerecke was not as hostile towards Catholicism and got along very well with his Catholic counterpart during the trials.)

title: hiroshima
body:
The main city of [[Hiroshima perfecture]], [[Japan]]. Historically a major port and maritime hub of the country.

Widely remembered for [[atomic_bombings_of_hiroshima_and_nagasaki|being the target of the first ever nuclear weapon attack]] in August 6, 1945. The [[B-29 superfortress]] [[bomber]] [i]Enola Gay[/i] dropped the [[nuclear weapon|atomic bomb]] "[[Little Boy (bomb)|]]", a nearly 1 short ton (9,700 pounds) Uranium device with a blast yield of 15 kilotons, in the early morning of that day.

h4. See also

* [[Hiroshimaben]]
* [[Hiroshima Peace Memorial]]
* [[Nagasaki]]

title: hakos_baelz_(1st_costume)
body:
The default costume of [[hololive English]]'s [[Hakos Baelz]].

It consists of [[black collar|black]], [[spiked collar]], [[white shirt]] [[crop top]] with with [[mismatched sleeves|mismatched]] [[short over long sleeves]] and a stylized "RAT" [[clothes writing|printed]] on it, worn over a [[black tube top]], a [[single glove|single]] [[black gloves|black glove]], a [[thigh strap]], a [[multicolored skirt|multicolored]] [[miniskirt]] and [[mismatched legwear]] (a red [[single loose sock|loose sock]] and a yellow [[single kneehigh|kneehigh]] and [[black shoes]].

While her top was canonically meant to be a [[strapless shirt]] with [[detached sleeves]] (based on her 3D model in post #6813553), due to the ambiguity in her reference sheet it is depicted quite inconsistently in fanart and even in official art, often being depicted as an [[off-shoulder shirt]] with the white sleeves attached (as seen in post #4984329), Due to frequent mistagging, and for the sake of tag consistency only tag is [[off-shoulder shirt]] if the sleeves are visibly attached to and [[strapless shirt]] only if the sleeves are clearly detached.

h4. Appearance

* !post #6813553: 3D model
* !post #4724951: Reference sheet

title: carl_johnson
body:
The protagonist of [i][[Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas]][/i]. Known as "CJ" for short.

A key member of the Grove Street Families, he left in 1987 after moving to Liberty City after his younger brother Brian died, only to return in 1992 after his mother's death. After being blackmailed by corrupt police officer [[Frank Tenpenny]], CJ underwent journey across the state of San Andreas in order to build his criminal profile and fought back against the law.

The meme "[[Ah shit here we go again (meme)|]]." was uttered by him.

title: masters_of_the_universe
body:
[i][b]Masters of the Universe[/b][/i] (commonly abbreviated [i][b]MOTU[/b][/i] and sometimes referred to as [i][b]He-Man and the Masters of the Universe[/b][/i] or just [i][b]He-Man[/b][/i], after the lead hero) is a [[science fiction]] and [[fantasy]] American media franchise created by the "Mattel toy company":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mattel in the early 80s.

Although featuring a vast line-up of characters, the main premise revolves around the conflict between the heroic [[He-Man]] and the evil [[Skeletor]] on [[eternia_(planet)|planet Eternia]]. 

Since its initial launch, the franchise has spawned a variety of products, including six lines of [[action figure]]s, four animated television series, several comic series, and a live action feature film (The "Japanese title":https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E3%83%9E%E3%82%B9%E3%82%BF%E3%83%BC%E3%82%BA/%E8%B6%85%E7%A9%BA%E3%81%AE%E8%A6%87%E8%80%85 is usually only used for the movie).

The first cartoon series was broadcasted from 1983 to 1985. It became extremely popular in several different countries. 

A second animated spin-off series called [[She-Ra Princess of Power|She-Ra: Princess of Power]] was released in 1985. It also became quite popular, but not as much as the first series. It was rebooted in 2018 as [[She-Ra and the Princesses of Power]].

Designer Roger Sweet claims to be the chief creator of He-Man and MOTU, although this is not officially acknowledged by Mattel and is disputed by some other contributors. The earliest storybooks and much of the original backstory were written by Donald F. Glut, while the final production sculpt of the very first 1982 He-Man [[action figure]] was done by Tony Guerrero.

title: liliweiss_(nikke)
body:
An NPC from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]].

Also known as [b]Lilith[/b], she was the first Nikke ever created to fight the [[Rapture (nikke)|]]s and the former leader of the dissolved [[Goddess (nikke)|]] squad.

[spoilers]During Operation Ark Guardian (Over Zone), Liliweiss died of unspecified causes and was buried in a casket near the vicinity of the Ark on the surface. Later on, her grave was found and desecrated by the Raptures and her head was stolen, leading to [[Snow White (nikke)|]]'s second mind switch and descent into destroying Raptures with extreme prejudice, whom the former sees her as a hero.[/spoilers]

Unlike her squadmates whose name were based on fairy tales, her name, albeit nickname, is a reference from the "Jewish and Mesopotamian mythological figure of the same name":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lilith].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[white hair]] and [[blue eyes]] with [[star-shaped pupils]]. Her outfit is a [[military uniform]] consisting of [[black jacket]], [[black capelet]], a pair of [[white gloves]] and a [[black pantyhose]].
other_names: リリーバイス(勝利の女神:NIKKE)

title: red_hood_(nikke)
body:
A playable character in [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]] and a member of the ill-fated legendary [[Goddess (nikke)|]] squad along with [[Liliweiss (nikke)|]], [[Snow White (nikke)|]],  [[Rapunzel (pure grace) (nikke)|Rapunzel]], [[Scarlet (Black Shadow) (nikke)|Scarlet]], and [[Dorothy (nikke)|]].

The last Grimms model joining the Goddess squad. She's a bold and cheerful Nikke who loves old songs. Her red hair, red scarf, and red jacket are unforgettable.

She has a hobby listening to old music and consuming adult material such as erotic novels and dirty magazines. The latter tendency often got her into fights with the strait-laced [[Rapunzel (nikke)|Rapunzel]], who tried to curtail it.

[spoiler]She was formerly assimilated within [[Rapi (nikke)|]] but, as of chapter 26, has disappeared with no possible way of returning. [/spoiler]

Much like her squadmates, Red hood was named after the character from the "European fairy tale of the same name, albeit clipped":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Little_Red_Riding_Hood].

Illustrator: [[mikan03 26]]

title: otome_game_no_hametsu_flag_shika_nai_akuyaku_reijou_ni_tensei_shite_shimatta
body:
English title: "My Next Life as a Villainess: All Routes Lead to Doom!"

An isekai story about a tomboyish otaku gamer who is reincarnated in to the villainous rival of the heroine in the game she played.  Being focused upon avoiding the Bad End flags of her story to the point of being oblivious to all else, the girl doesn't realize she's ruined the story by having a personality that out-heroines the original heroine and successfully builds a "reverse harem" for herself by mistake.

Illustrated by [[Hidaka Nami]].

h4. Characters

* [[Katarina Claes]] - Main character - [[aqua eyes]] in strong [[tsurime]] shape, [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] with [[swept bangs]], a [[hair ribbon]] and [[hairclip|barrette]].
* [[Anne Shelley]] - Main character's [[maid]] - [[short hair|short]] [[red hair]], [[swept bangs]].
* [[Geordo Stuart]] - 3rd prince/main character's fiancee - [[blonde hair]], [[swept bangs]], [[hair between eyes]], and [[blue eyes]].
* [[Keith Claes]] - Main character's younger brother - [[brown hair|brown]] [[wavy hair]] with [[parted bangs]] and [[sidelocks]], [[sanpaku]] [[aqua eyes]].
* [[Mary Hunt]] - Katarina's friend - [[yuri]] romantic interest - [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair|brown]]/[[red hair]], [[swept bangs]], and [[brown eyes|brown]]/[[red eyes]].
* [[Alan Stuart]] - 4th prince and Mary's (supposed) fiancee - [[grey hair]], [[asymmetrical bangs]], and [[blue eyes]].
* [[Sophia Ascart]] - Katarina's friend - [[very long hair|very long]] [[white hair]], [[hair ribbon]], [[blunt bangs]], [[red eyes]] in [[tareme]] style.
* [[Nicol Ascart]] - Sophia's brother - [[black eyes]], [[black hair]], [[asymmetrical bangs]] with [[hair between eyes]].
* [[Maria Campbell]] - Original heroine - [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] with [[hair flower|hair flowers]], [[green eyes|green]] [[tareme]] eyes.
* [[Raphael Wolt]] - [spoiler]"Sirius Dieke", student council president[/spoiler] - [[red hair|red]] [[curly hair]], [[grey eyes]].

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: My Next Life as a Villainess: All Routes Lead to Doom!":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/My_Next_Life_as_a_Villainess:_All_Routes_Lead_to_Doom!]
* "Wikipedia (JP):乙女ゲームの破滅フラグしかない悪役令嬢に転生してしまった…":[https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%B9%99%E5%A5%B3%E3%82%B2%E3%83%BC%E3%83%A0%E3%81%AE%E7%A0%B4%E6%BB%85%E3%83%95%E3%83%A9%E3%82%B0%E3%81%97%E3%81%8B%E3%81%AA%E3%81%84%E6%82%AA%E5%BD%B9%E4%BB%A4%E5%AC%A2%E3%81%AB%E8%BB%A2%E7%94%9F%E3%81%97%E3%81%A6%E3%81%97%E3%81%BE%E3%81%A3%E3%81%9F%E2%80%A6]

title: mirai_akari
body:
[[Virtual YouTuber]]. A cheery, social girl who was one of the [[virtual youtuber shiten'nou|first large Virtual YouTubers]] after [[Kizuna Ai]]. Slightly pervy. She was originally managed by [[Eilene]] until mid-2018, belonged to [[ENTUM]] until it shut down at the end of 2019, and joined GOOM STUDIO afterward in late 2020. After more than five years, she announced she was "retiring":https://twitter.com/MiraiAkari_prj/status/1639190621373231106/photo/1 at the end of March 2023, due to creative differences with her management, among other things.

[spoiler]The "Former Shiten'nou" would reincarnate under [[Sony Music Virtual]] as [[Aglio Olio e Peperoncino]], though initially this connection would not be shown explicitly until "later":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=doVCVgN9O9E&t=1132s].[/spoiler]

Character design by [[KEI (keigarou)|]].

title: kaguya_luna
body:
[b]Kaguya Luna[/b] is a [[Virtual YouTuber]] who made her debut on December 9, 2017. She was managed by Vic inc. from the start, but between fall 2018 and fall 2019, she operated under her own autonomous agency, [[THE MOON STUDIO]]. In addition to her YouTube content, she produced music under the Sony Music label [[SACRA MUSIC]]. She was designed by [[Mika Pikazo]].

While neither she nor Vic Inc. have officially announced that she had graduated, her most recent YouTube video was published on August 29th, 2020, and the Kaguya Luna Official channel has been inactive ever since. Kaguya Luna's Twitter account has not been active since October 20th, 2020, and as of the end of 2021, the Kaguya Luna Fan Club website has shut down.

Her voice was often compared to [[Hamtaro]], earning her the nickname "Strangled Hamtaro" (首を絞めたハム太郎).

[spoiler][[Pmaru-sama]], who has "admitted":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ADVUKyyq3uA] she is the talent behind Kaguya Luna, remains very active with her own channel on YouTube.[/spoiler]

title: mouar_pharaoh
body:
[quote][i]"I said I'd be by your side, Jerid..."[/i] - Mouar Pharaoh[/quote]

A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. She appears in the [[Zeta Gundam]] anime TV series from 1985. 

One of [[Jerid Messa]]'s love interests and a [[titans_(gundam)|Titans]] [[mobile_suit|MS]] pilot. Her mecha of choice are the [[Hizack]] and the [[Gabthley]]. 

[spoilers]Goes the way of the dodo via [[Kamille Bidan]], like many others. She takes a direct beam shot from [[zeta_gundam_(mobile_suit)|Kamille's Zeta Gundam]] intended for Jerid, successfully saving him but also dying in the process.[/spoilers]

title: lila_milla_rira
body:
A fictional female character from the [[Gundam]] series. She first appeared in [[Zeta Gundam]] from 1985. 

A regular [[Earth Federation Space Forces]] veteran who isn't too fond of the [[titans_(gundam)|Titans]] but fights alongside them anyway because she is ordered to do so. 

[b]Lila Milla Rira[/b] is a skillful veteran [[mecha]] [[pilot]], able to control the notoriously finicky [[Galbaldy Beta]] [[mobile suit]]. [spoiler]However, even her experience and skills are not enough to defeat [[Kamille Bidan]] in his [[Gundam Mk II]] mobile suit who shots her down in a [[space]] [[duel]] early in the series, Lila realizing in her last moments how helpless "oldtypes" are against the powers of "newtypes" like Kamille. This encounter would worsen the animosity between Kamille and [[Jerid Messa]] even further, as Jerid was secretely in love with the older woman.[/spoiler]
other_names: ライラ・ミラ・ライラ

title: grunt_(warcraft)
body:
Grunts are the basic warriors of the Horde and the orcish clans. They are typically equipped with mighty axes and battle-worn armor.

Grunts appeared as units on the orc or Horde side in Warcraft, Warcraft II and Warcraft III. They are the classic counterpart to human footmen but are stronger than them in Warcraft III. They do, however, cost much more. In all the strategy games they are voiced by Bill Roper.

title: alter_servant
body:
Theoretical fan-designed [[dark persona]] version of a character who has been (theoretically) corrupted by the mud of the Fuyuki Holy Grail from [[Fate/Stay Night]], similar to canon examples like [[Dark Sakura]] or [[Saber Alter]]. Fan examples of "alters" include [[Archer Alter (fate)|]], [[Lancer Alter]] (later made [[cu_chulainn_alter_(fate)|canon]] in [[Fate/Grand Order]]), or the "Sabatsugu" version of [[Emiya Kiritsugu]] (not to be confused with [[Emiya Kiritsugu (Assassin)]]).

Common traits of an Alter version of a character include [[white hair]], [[red eyes]] or [[yellow eyes]], [[pale skin]], and visible red veins of [[corruption]]. Alter characters will also typically be dressed in an [[alternate costume]] with darker colors or stripes of black and red.

In the later installments, the concept of Alter Servant is expanded to include any servant that were corrupted or have their saint graph altered to some degree without the Holy Grail involved. Notable examples include [[Atalanta Alter (fate)|]] who is essentially an alternate noble phantasm form of [[Atalanta (fate)|]] and retains the same personality.

The opposite of this is [[Lily Servant]].

Not to be used for official Alters, which include:

title: emphasis_lines
body:
Lines drawn in a burst pattern, radiating outward from a part of the image to which the artist wants to draw attention. They cause the area surrounded by the lines to stand out more in the viewer's eye.

These are not the same as [[speed lines]], which indicate fast motion; emphasis lines indicate [i]focus[/i], rather than motion.

A similar technique used in filmography is to focus the camera toward a specific part of the shot (sometimes off-center) while allowing other parts of the image to become unfocused, thus drawing extra attention to the focused area.

h4. Examples

* !post #2174421

h4. See also

* [[hatching (texture)]]
* [[notice lines]]
* [[shout lines]]
* [[vignetting]]

title: zenshuu
body:
An original Japanese anime television series produced by [[studio mappa|MAPPA]], distributed overseas by [[crunchyroll]]. 

Centers around [[Hirose Natsuko]], an up-and-coming prodigy in the world of animation, who has recently been assigned her first role as director- “a romantic comedy centered around first love”. However, Natsuko finds herself unable to write the story, being a recluse who has no interest in romance or friendship.

One day, after succumbing to food poisoning, Natsuko wakes up in the world of the movie that made her fall in love with animation- a bleak tragedy centered around the end of the world. To avoid dying alongside them, Natsuko must work with the movie’s characters to change its bleak ending, growing closer to them in the process.

title: kampfer
body:
[i]For the [[mecha]] from [[Gundam 0080]], see [[Kampfer (Mobile Suit)]].[/i]

[b]Kämpfer[/b] (German for "Fighter") is a light novel series by Tsukiji Toshihiko, with illustrations by [[Senmu (senmudayo)|]]. The series contains 15 volumes published by [i]Media Factory[/i] under their [i]MF Bunko J[/i] imprint between November 2006 and March 2010. The main series covers 12 volumes, while the remaining three are short story collections. A manga adaptation by [[Tachibana Yuu]] started serialization in the April 2008 issue of [i]Monthly Comic Alive[/i]. A 12-episode anime adaptation aired in Japan between October and December 2009 on [i]TBS[/i], concluded in spring 2011 with [i]Kämpfer für die Liebe[/i]. The series has extensive use of the German language.

h4. Plot

[[Senou Natsuru]] discovered that he can morph into a female fighter (Kämpfer) after receiving a plush doll gift from his friend, [[Sakura Kaede]]. Suddenly, he discovered himself in a deadly fight between Kämpfers. The party responsible for the fight is rumored to be as Moderators and they are mysterious.

h4. Characters

title: ryuujou_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Japanese light carrier [i]Ryuujou[/i].
Character design by [[Kinjo Kuromomo]], voiced by [[Suzaki Aya]].

h4. Appearance
Her base art portrays her with [[short hair|short]] [[pink hair]], [[dragon horns]], [[dragon tail]], and [[green eyes]], in line with her name (meaning "prancing dragon").

Her outfit consists of a white [[midriff]] with [[white sailor collar]], a white [[military uniform]] coat with traditional [[long sleeves]], a red [[hakama short skirt]], [[rudder footwear]], and dragon scales-themed [[socks]]. Her rig consists of her real-life [[flight deck]] to her right and her bridge and three bow pieces on her left.

h4. History
In real life, [i]Ryuujou[/i] was designed to exploit a loophole in the original Washington Naval Treaty that excluded carriers from total tonnage if they weighed 8,000 tons or less. To that end, she was given a slim cruiser hull, no armor, and a single hangar. However, the 1930 London Naval Treaty closed the loophole, while IJN planners insisted on doubling her air group so a second hangar was placed atop the original, leaving her as the only ship of her class and suffering from questionable seakeeping and stability. She was rebuilt after sustaining storm damage in 1935.

At the start of the war, she was the only carrier available to the IJN for Southeast Asian combat support operations (while the Kido Butai did provide support in the Dutch East Indies, they only did so when needed). Alongside [[Junyou (Azur Lane)|]], they participated in the Aleutians campaign before transferring to Guadalcanal. She was sunk by aircraft from [[Saratoga (Azur Lane)|]] in the battle of the Eastern Solomons in late August 1942.

title: bohemian_rhapsody
body:
1975 rock song from the band [[Queen (Band)|]], famous for its music video, which includes a sequence of the four band members' faces lit up in darkness, arranged in a diamond pattern.

(Although the oft-parodied image, with the bottom figure crossing their arms in an X, is actually taken from the cover of their album "Queen II":[https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/43/Queen_II_%28album_cover%29.jpg].)

There is also a 2018 biopic movie of the same name, which dramatizes the group from their formation to their famous performance at Live Aid in 1985.

title: green_rose
body:
A type of [[rose]] that does not occur in nature. Symbolism for this flower is not widely identified but could be associated with common themes for green, such as fertility and jealousy.

Most bred variety of green roses only feature a slight green tint to their flower color, this is due to having chlorophyll in the petals.  Rosa chinensis 'Viridiflora' also known as the "green rose" is a case where the due to mutation the petals of the rose have been replaced with leafs.

title: palette_knife
body:
For tagging purposes this tag covers both [i]palette knives[/i] and [i]painting knives[/i].  Both are blunt [[spatula]]-like or [[trowel]]-like [[knife|knives]] used in [[painting_(action)|]] to mix and spread paint.

A [i]palette knife[/i] is a spatula-like knife with a long straight blunt blade with a rounded tip, unlike a painting knife which has angular shapes.  It is used to mix paints and scrape paint on the canvas. Examples: post #1200056, post #1210470.

A [i]painting knife[/i] is a trowel-like knife with a pointed tip and blunt blade of different lengths and shapes, such as triangular, rectangular, or diamond-like. It is used to take paint from the [[paint palette]] and apply it to the canvas.  Examples: post #487692, post #1410484.

For the confectionary tool, see [i][[icing spatula]][/i].

h4. Example

* !post #8090730

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia - Palette knife":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palette_knife]
* "Wikipedia - Painting knife":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Painting_knife]

title: ran_ran_ru
body:
Ran Ran Ru (ランランルー, [i]Ran Ran Ruu[/i]) is a dance move performed by Donald McDonald, the Japanese interpretation of [[Ronald McDonald]], in a commercial for a mid-2000s [[McDonald's]] advertising campaign known as "Ronald Rumors" (ドナルドのうわさ, [i]Donald no uwasa[/i]), where he answered questions about himself.

The move is done in three steps:
* The hands are crossed and tapped on their opposite shoulders once. Donald says a single [i]ran[/i].
* The hands are clapped together once. Donald says a single [i]ran[/i].
* The hands are raised up straight and above the head. Donald finishes with a single extended [i]ruu![/i]

The move became a staple parody of fan artists, especially in Japan, with the Japanese video sharing site NicoNico being a particular hotspot for parody videos. One such video would have him do the dance in tune to [[Flandre Scarlet]]'s theme "U.N. Owen was her?" (referred to as McDonald Insanity or McRoll'd), which would go particularly viral and have Donald associated with Flandre.

The advertising campaign would feature other commercials that would similarly go viral, such as him showing a different dance, him posing in front of a mirror, him falling backwards on a park bench after taking a phone call, and him playing baseball.

On Danbooru, this tag is primarily used for any character seen to be performing or demonstrating the Ran Ran Ru dance, but references to the other commercials in the Ronald Rumors campaign can also be tagged with it.

h4. See Also

* [[Ronald McDonald]]
* [[Ero aru yo (meme)]]

h4. External links

* "Internet Archive: Donald Rumors":[https://archive.org/details/McDonaldsJapaneseCMRonaldMcDonald] (Ran Ran Ru at 3:04)

title: j.k._simmons
body:
Jonathan Kimble Simmon (born January 9, 1955) is an American actor. 
Simmons is known for his role as J. Jonah Jameson in Sam Raimi's [[Spider-Man]] trilogy (2002–2007). He reprised his role as Jameson in various Marvel media unrelated to the Raimi trilogy, including multiple animated titles and the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] films. He has appeared in numerous supporting roles in films such as The Cider House Rules (1999), Thank You for Smoking (2005), Juno (2007), Burn After Reading (2008), Up in the Air (2009), Jennifer's Body (2009), [[La La Land]] (2016), Justice League (2017), Palm Springs (2020), and Juror No. 2 (2024), playing iterations of [[Santa Claus]] in Klaus (2019) and Red One (2024). He portrayed William Frawley in Being the Ricardos (2021), for which he received another nomination for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor.

On television he is known for playing white supremacist prisoner Vernon Schillinger on the HBO series Oz (1997–2003), the recurring role of Dr. Emil Skoda on the NBC series [[Law & Order]] (1997–2010), Assistant Police Chief Will Pope on the TNT series The Closer (2005–2012), and Howard Silk in the Starz series Counterpart (2017–2019). He also appeared in commercials for Farmers Insurance.
As a voice actor he is known for portraying the [[yellow (m&m's)|Yellow M&M]] in commercials since 1996, Cave Johnson in the video game [[Portal 2]] (2011), White Knight in [[Generator Rex]] (2010–2013), Tenzin in [[The Legend of Korra]] (2012–2014), Stanford "Ford" Pines in [[Gravity Falls]] (2015–2016), Kai in [[Kung fu panda|Kung Fu Panda 3]] (2016), Mayor Leodore Lionheart in [[Zootopia]] (2016), Martin Smarty in [[Kim Possible]] (2002–2007), [[Nolan Grayson]] / [[Omni-Man]] in [[invincible (series)|Invincible]] (2021–present) and Mortal Kombat 1 (2023), and General Ketheric Thorm in the video game Baldur's Gate 3 (2023).

title: whiplash_(2014_movie)
body:
Whiplash is a 2014 psychological drama film directed by Damien Chazelle. The film follows [[Andrew Neiman]], played by Miles Teller, an ambitious music student and aspiring jazz drummer who is pushed to his limits by [[Terence Fletcher]], played by [[J.K. Simmons]], an abusive music conductor and perfectionist for the fictional Shaffer Conservatory in [[New York City]]. The film explores concepts of perfectionism, dedication, and success and deconstructs the concept of ambition.

The film won several awards including Best Supporting Actor for J.K. Simmons during the 87th Academy Awards.

Japanese title: [i]Session[/i]

title: hornet_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s depiction of the US aircraft carrier USS [i]Hornet[/i] (CV-8). Character design by [[Hao (patinnko)|]], voiced by Yamamoto Nozomi.

Hornet's design differs markedly from her sisters on account of the fact that she was the first carrier built post-treaty. Instead of the white hair and silver/blue eyes of her sisters, Hornet has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] tied into a pair of [[twintails]] and [[green eyes]]. She is also more dressed down than her sisters. Her attire consists of a [[black bikini|black]] [[bikini top only|bikini top]], a pair of [[short shorts]], and [[black thighhighs]]. She sports a pair of black [[fingerless gloves|fingerless]] [[elbow gloves]] that stop right before the knuckle and have a yellow stripe along their length, as well as a dashing [[cowboy hat]], with a [[yellow belt]] and underside. She has a long [[black coat]] similar to Enterprise, marked with the number 8 as well as her ship name. 

Her [[rigging]] is composed of her [[flight deck]], missing the yellow markings of her sisters as well as the island superstructure combined with the flight deck. On the deck itself are 2 [[B-25 Mitchell|B-25 Mitchells]], a reference to the Doolittle Raid.

title: tiananmen_square_copypasta
body:
A [[meme]] copypasta containing various known blacklisted words of the of the [[china|Chinese]] internet censorship algorithm. The original intent of the copypasta is to cause any internet user from mainland China to get blocked after the censorship algorithm detects such keywords.

A Chinese equivalent of the copypasta existed in the form of the Zhao Bomb Magnet (赵弹磁铁), a text generator which could implicate whomever you were talking to of supporting things the government opposed, in the ultimate hope of getting the other user to delete their account to avoid being associated with it. The Zhao Bomb Magnet existed for slightly over a year before it got taken down, with its creator going dark at around the same time.

h4. Full copypasta

[quote]
动态网自由门 天安門 天安门 法輪功 李洪志 Free Tibet 六四天安門事件 The Tiananmen Square protests of 1989 天安門大屠殺 The Tiananmen Square Massacre 反右派鬥爭 The Anti-Rightist Struggle 大躍進政策 The Great Leap Forward 文化大革命 The Great Proletarian Cultural Revolution 人權 Human Rights 民運 Democratization 自由 Freedom 獨立 Independence 多黨制 Multi-party system 台灣 臺灣 Taiwan Formosa 中華民國 Republic of China 西藏 土伯特 唐古特 Tibet 達賴喇嘛 Dalai Lama 法輪功 Falun Dafa 新疆維吾爾自治區 The Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region 諾貝爾和平獎 Nobel Peace Prize 劉暁波 Liu Xiaobo 民主 言論 思想 反共 反革命 抗議 運動 騷亂 暴亂 騷擾 擾亂 抗暴 平反 維權 示威游行 李洪志 法輪大法 大法弟子 強制斷種 強制堕胎 民族淨化 人體實驗 肅清 胡耀邦 趙紫陽 魏京生 王丹 還政於民 和平演變 激流中國 北京之春 大紀元時報 九評論共産黨 獨裁 專制 壓制 統一 監視 鎮壓 迫害 侵略 掠奪 破壞 拷問 屠殺 活摘器官 誘拐 買賣人口 遊進 走私 毒品 賣淫 春畫 賭博 六合彩 天安門 天安门 法輪功 李洪志 Winnie the Pooh 劉曉波动态网自由门
[/quote]

h4. See also

* [[Tag Group:Text]]
* [[Tiananmen Square]]
* [[wall of text]]

h4. External links

* "Know Your Meme":[https://knowyourmeme.com/editorials/guides/what-is-the-tiananmen-square-copypasta-the-censorship-hack-to-silence-gamers-explained]

title: hcaptcha
body:
A [[CAPTCHA]] service that websites use to verify users are human rather than automated bots. It presents visual or interactive challenges that are typically easy for humans but difficult for automated programs to solve.

hCaptcha gained significant popularity after [[Google]] began charging for high volumes of [[reCAPTCHA]] usage, and it's now used by millions of websites worldwide to prevent spam, account takeovers, and other automated attacks.

h4. External links
* "Official website":[https://www.hcaptcha.com/]

title: anatomical_nonsense
body:
A depiction of a character's body that flagrantly defies common sense, especially to comedic effect. This does not mean "[[bad anatomy]], but even worse!", nor does it cover conventional stylizations like [[chibi]]; it represents a conscious total disregard both for realistic anatomy and for the usual stylistic deviations therefrom.

Absurd proportions are often used for comedic effect, but may very well also be a serious artistic choice, often seen in art genres like [[surreal|surrealism]] and [[cubism]]. 

h4. Examples
* !post #7213707: extremely [[long neck]]
* !post #8691614: anatomical nonsense in [[cubism]]
* !post #2995838: extremely [[small head]]
* !post #3134223: face-body mismatch 

h4. See Also

* [[body horror]]
* [[engineering nonsense]]
* [[misplaced genitals]]
* [[what]]
* pool #1908, "What Has Science Done?!?"

title: yamcha_pose_(meme)
body:
A reference to a scene from [[Dragon Ball]] where [[Yamcha]] was crumpled up in a [[crater]] after being caught in a [[Saibaiman|Saibaman's]] self-destruction attack.  The pose has become memetic as a way of expressing comically defeated characters in fanart and doujins.  

* !asset #22633450

The pose itself involves the character laying down on their right side, face pointed away and viewed feet-first, and with limbs curled halfway into a fetal position. The character in the pose is usually in a smoking crater, even if whatever put them in the Yamcha pose wasn't even an explosive.

h4. See also

* [[family guy death pose (meme)|Family Guy Death Pose]]


h4. External links

* "Know Your Meme: Yamcha's Death Pose":http://knowyourmeme.com/memes/yamchas-death-pose

title: small_head
body:
When a character has a noticeably too small head.

Good examples are certain [[one_piece|One Piece]] characters.

The best way to find small head posts are to see how many heads tall they are. The average human is generally 7-and-a-half heads tall (including the head). 

h4. Examples

(All including head)
* !post #7827094: Approximately 9 heads tall.
* !post #7489996: Approximately 9.5 heads tall.
* !post #4141598: Almost 6 heads from head to thighs.
* !post #4293671: Comedically small. ([[Anatomical nonsense]])

title: tribe_nine
body:
A Japanese multimedia franchise created by Too Kyo Games, under the direction of Kodaka Kazutaka (who also created [[Danganronpa (series)|]] under Spike Chunsoft), and Akatsuki. It consists of an anime of the same name produced by Liden Films that aired between January-March 2022, a webtoon series with the subtitle "War of Tokyo"[tn](トライブナイン/ウォー・オブ・トーキョー)[/tn] that ran between December 2022 up to sometime in 2023, and an action role-playing gacha game first announced in 2020 and officially released globally on February 20, 2025 for mobile and PC via Steam.

The anime mainly followed the stories of the rebellious Tribes and their many battles, with Extreme Baseball (XB) as the battleground, in the cyberpunk mega-city of Neo Tokyo.

The game is set around two years after the events of the anime, mainly following amnesiac aspiring XB player [[Kuronaka Yo]] and his team, the Trash Tribe, as they battle against Neo Tokyo's newest and most dangerous tyrant [[Zero (Tribe Nine)|Zero]], as well as nine other dangerous individuals called NUMBERS, in both his "favorite" death games called Extreme Games (XG) and in XB, in order to free Neo Tokyo from his clutches.

title: vesti_(nikke)
body:
A character from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]].

She is a member of [[Absolute (nikke)|]], Elysion's most powerful squad along with [[Emma (nikke)|]] and [[Eunhwa (nikke)|]]. Despite her reputation as Absolute's strongest member, Vesti is shy and timid, wanting nothing more than to make friends.

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[medium hair|medium]] [[grey hair]] along with [[medium breasts]]. Her outfit consists of a [[beret]], [[black jacket]] with [[red necktie]], [[cape]], [[black shorts]] and a pair of [[thigh boots]].
h4. Skins

title: eunhwa_(nikke)
body:
A playable character in [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]]. 

The leader of the [[Absolute (nikke)|]] squad who evokes an air of both arrogance and composure. Her perfectionism has pushed Absolute up to the pinnacle of success. The Absolute squad consists of Eunhwa herself, [[Emma (nikke)|]] and [[Vesti (nikke)|]].

[spoiler]Originally a human commander who was ditched by her own Nikkes after deeming her an amateur, she was wiped out by a Rapture attack including her own Nikkes. After befriending [[Rapi (nikke)|]] as a Nikke from Absolute, both Eunhwa and Rapi became the "perfect partner" until Rapi accidentally murdered a human with one of her explosives during a mission. Her departure from the squad without official leave has left Eunhwa betrayed and has since been embittered by Rapi's departure.[/spoiler]

She has [[purple eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] with [[asymmetrical bangs]] showing off her [[forehead]]. She wears a [[black headwear|black]] [[beret]], a [[black leotard|black]] [[collared leotard]] under a [[black serafuku]] with a [[red neckerchief]], and a [[black jacket|black]] [[hooded jacket|hooded]] [[jacket]] on top of that.

Illustrator: [[Hyulla]]

h4. Official Art

* !post #5953741: L2D

title: malva_(pokemon)
body:
[[pokemon xy|Kalos]] Elite Four member and a Fire-type master.
Also a member of [[Team Flare]].

[[Queen Sectonia]] merges with this plant for the final boss fight of that game, but is defeated by [[Kirby]], with help of [[Taranza]] and [[King Dedede]]. It is a landmark in Dream Land ever since.

body:

Claycia is friends with [[elline_(kirby)|Elline]], who paints the clay sculptures that she makes. This changed when she fell under the control of [[Dark Crafter]] via a pair of [[sunglasses]] prior to the game's events, in a manner similar to that of [[dark_matter_(kirby)|Dark Matter]]. Seventopia, her origin game's main setting, is her creation, made with the colors stolen from Planet [[Planet Popstar]]
H4. See also

title: master_crown
body:
An ancient artifact in the [i][[Kirby (series)|]][/i] games, introduced in [i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land]][/i]. It is said to give its wearer unlimited power.

[spoiler]The main story of [i]Kirby's Return to Dream Land[/i] is driven by [[Magolor]]'s efforts to steal the Crown from its current guardian, [[Landia]]. After enlisting the help of [[Kirby]] [[king_dedede|and]] [[meta_knight|his]] [[bandana_waddle_dee|friends]], he succeeds in doing so and attempts to conquer the universe, starting with [[Planet Popstar]]. The Crown's influence and evil sentience get the better of him and he transforms into a [[magolor_soul|monster]] that is swiftly defeated by Kirby and company.[/spoiler]

[spoiler][[Void Termina]] is able to summon the Crown (or at least a replica of it) during his boss battle in [i][[Kirby: Star Allies]][/i]. This along with the Jambastion sigil closely resembling the Crown suggests a strong connection with him, [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], and the twisted treasure.[/spoiler]

[spoiler][i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land Deluxe]][/i] confirms that the Master Crown is in fact, sentient, having brought the downfall of multiple civilizations in the past. In the [i][[Magolor Epilogue]][/i], it first enhances the [[Grand Doomer]] into the Crowned Doomer, then assimilates the [[Gem Apple]] to turn into [[master crown (tree)|a tree monster]] before being poetically struck down by Magolor’s [[Ultra Sword]].[/spoiler]

title: magolor
body:
A character in [i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land]][/i]. Known as [b]Mahoroa[/b] in the Japanese release. He enlists the help of [[Kirby]] [[king_dedede|and]] [[meta_knight|his]] [[bandana_waddle_dee|friends]] to repair his spaceship, the [[Lor Starcutter]].

[spoiler]His true motives are hardly mentioned until the very end of the main story, where it is revealed that he really wanted to steal the [[Master Crown]] from its guardian, [[Landia]]. After he succeeds, he tries to conquer the universe, starting with [[Planet Popstar]]. Fortunately, Kirby and company are able to stop him.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]After his defeat, he surprisingly tries to make amends with Kirby, and reveals he may have been used as a puppet by the Master Crown itself.[/spoiler] He starts by building an amusement park for the puffball's 20th anniversary, and he continues to provide support for future adventures, including running a shop in [i][[Team Kirby Clash Deluxe]][/i] and being a Dream Friend in [i][[kirby:_star_allies|Kirby Star Allies]][/i].

h4. See Also

* [spoiler][[Master Crown]][/spoiler]

* [spoiler][[Hyness]][/spoiler]

* [[Magolor Epilogue]]

title: kirby_64
body:
A direct sequel to [[Kirby's Dream Land 3]], despite the name not making that very clear.

One day, the peaceful world of [[Ripple Star]] is attacked by [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], which quickly begins to cover the planet in darkness. In a last-ditch effort, the [[Ripple Star Queen]] sends a fairy named [[Ribbon (kirby)|]] away to protect the treasured Crystal. Ribbon manages to escape, but not before having the Crystal shattered in an ambush from Dark Matter.

Ribbon crashes down on [[Planet Popstar]], right on top of [[Kirby]] as he was watching the night sky. Sharing her problems with him, the carefeee hero gladly decides to help out. The two then set out on another adventure, recruiting a few friends along the way!

One of the game's main mechanics is Kirby's ability to combine [[Copy Ability|Copy Abilities]] together called [[Power Combo (kirby)|]], giving him unique combat abilities, such as "wielding a fire sword":[/posts/7554641] or "maneuvering a giant drill":[/posts/334573]

title: m16
body:
An American-designed 5.56x45mm [[assault rifle]], developed in 1957 by Eugene Stoner at ArmaLite and based on his previous [[AR-10]] design. The [[rifle]] had initial bad notoriety due to the original design's tendency to jam with dirt or in some weather conditions, but is also regarded effective thanks to its low weight and high accuracy.

It has been the standard weapon of the US military since 1964, and has been partially replaced by the [[M4 Carbine]]. Visually distinguishable by its triangular front sight and integrated carrying handle/rear sight, although newer variants (such as the shortened [[M4 carbine]] version) sport removable units. 

This tag is for M16-type rifles used in military-related context. For the civilian-legal counterpart, see [[AR-15]].

h4. Major variants

* !post #1684456: [[M16A1]] and [[M16A2]].
* !post #3714287: [[M16A4]] - With Picatinny rails and removable carry handle.

title: ptrd-41
body:
The [b]PTRD-41[/b] is a [[Soviet]] single-shot, [[bolt action]] [[anti-materiel rifle]] chambered for 14.5×114mm [[rifle cartridge|cartridge]]. The weapon was designed by Vasily Degtyaryov as an easily-produced variant of the [[PTRS-41]], its production were started in 1941.

Extremely crude in design, the PTRD is made out of nothing more than a long metal barrel with a simple trigger mechanism. It was extensively used by the [[soviet army|Soviet Red Army]] during the [[World War II]]. It is notably the [[gun]] used by [[Suou Pavlichenko]] in [[Darker than Black]].

h4. See also

title: walther_wa_2000
body:
A semiautomatic [[bullpup]] [[sniper rifle]] produced by Ulm-based Walther from 1982 to 1988. 

Designed from the ground up as an advanced sniper weapon, the WA 2000 was built around its barrel and equipped with wooden furniture, a six-round magazine, and a unique self-leveling [[bipod]], resulting into its distinctive boxy, rectangular shape. It was produced in 3 calibers. 

Because of its complexity and high cost, only 176 all told were manufactured, making it a rare and very valuable [[gun]].

title: scene_fashion
body:
A fashion style similar to [[emo fashion]], but more colorful and over the top. It features many accessories in bright colors, cartoon designs, patterns, and a focus on fluffy, colorful hair.

Scene and emo are not mutually exclusive, and the two are often blurred, with this blur being referred to as "Scemo".

h4. Elements

Common clothing includes [[skinny jeans]], band [[t-shirt]]s and graphic tees, and [[tutu]]s. Accessories associated with the style are [[shutter shades]], [[studded belt]]s, [[fingerless gloves]], big [[hair bow]]s, [[bead necklace]]s and [[bead bracelet|bracelets]], rubber [[wristband]]s, and [[tiara]]s.

Hair is often fluffy with a fringe bang that falls [[hair over one eye|over one eye]] ([[scene cut]]). Some sections may be dyed with a [[raccoon tails (hairstyle)|repeating striped pattern]], or brightly colored [[streaked hair|streaks]].

Common visual motifs include [[gem (symbol)|]] shapes, patterns (checkered, horizontal stripes, [[animal print]], plaid), [[dinosaur]]s and [[zombie]]s. Cartoon characters are also popular, especially [[Hello Kitty (character)|]], [[GIR (Invader Zim)|]], [[Gloomy Bear]], and [[Domo-kun]].

In [[fighting game]]s, red ones usually represents that the move can deal hits and damage while other colors represents their hurtboxes or collision box.

In the [[Touhou]] games, it is represented by a small, white circle near the character's waist.

title: qixiong_ruqun
body:
Qixiong ruqun is a style of traditional Chinese clothing [[hanfu]], consisting of a long-sleeved blouse or jacket and a high-waisted skirt that reaches just below the armpits, covering the chest. It was most popular during the [[Tang Dynasty]] (618–907 CE) and is one of the best-known [[ruqun]] variations.

This style was commonly worn during periods of Han Chinese rule and is categorized as [[hanfu]]. It often featured flowing fabrics, intricate patterns, and vibrant colors, reflecting the aesthetic preferences of the Tang era.

Not to be confused with other forms of [[ruqun]].

Qixiong ruqun can be worn with or without a [[hezi]], note that [[heziqun]] is a separate from of hanfu which has a waistline below the bust. Heziqun is always worn with a hezi. 

H4. Examples

title: widow's_peak
body:
A V-shaped dip in the hairline in the middle of the [[forehead]], as opposed to a hairline that runs across the forehead in a straight line. [[Vegeta]], [[Mishima Kazuya]], and the [[joker (dc)|Joker]] are prominent examples of characters with distinctive widow's peaks.

A widow's peak is a natural facial feature. Don't use this tag just because of the way the hair is styled, e.g., because the character has [[hair intakes]] or a [[hair_strand|lock of hair]] lying across their forehead. This tag is not exclusive with [[bangs]], but enough of the hairline needs to be visible to confirm that a widow's peak is in fact present.

title: nekomata_okayu_(poisonya_syndrome)
body:
The 5th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Nekomata Okayu]]. It was unveiled during her 1st solo 3D live [i]"Poisonya Syndrome"[/i].

It consists of a puffy  [[black headwear|black]] [[beret]] with a [[rose]] [[hat flower|attached]], a [[black choker]], a [[collared shirt|colalred]] [[black shirt|black]] [[cropped shirt|cropped]] [[sleeveless shirt]] with multiple [[heart cutout]]s on her left breast, a [[two-tone jacket|two-tone]] ([[green jacket|green]] and [[purple jacket|purple]]) [[cropped jacket]] with [[shoulder cutout]]s, a diagonal [[breast zipper|zipper across her breasts]], a heart-shaped [[see-through clothes|see-through]] window over her left breast and [[mismatched sleeves]] with one of them being made out of  [[see-through sleeves|see-through]] [[fishnet sleeves|fishnets]], [[black shorts]] with a [[purple skirt|purple]] [[see-through skirt|see-through]] [[overskirt]], black [[garter straps]], [[mismatched legwear|mismatched]] [[purple thighhighs|purple]] [[over-kneehighs]] and [[black boots|black]] [[knee boots|knee-high]] [[fold-over boots|fold-over]] [[lace-up boots]].

For her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this costume, she has her [[long hair|longer]] [[official alternate hair length|than usual]] hair with a [[french braid]] [[half updo]] with [[diagonal bangs]].

h4. Appearance

title: nekomata_okayu_(wonderland)
body:
The 6th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Nekomata Okayu]].

It's inspired by the [[Cheshire Cat (alice in wonderland)|]] from [[Alice in Wonderland]] and consists of a [[black headwear|black]] [[beret]], a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white shirt]] with [[frilled sleeves]] and a [[cleavage cutout]], a [[purple ribbon|purple]] [[neck ribbon]], an optional [[black coat]] with a [[playing card theme]] [[stole]], [[black shorts]] with [[suspenders]]. [[grey socks|grey]], [[purple socks|purple]] and [[black socks|black]] [[striped socks|striped]] [[kneehighs]] held with [[legwear garter]]s and [[black shoes]]. The most peculiar detail of this costume, is a purple [[heart on chest|heart]] [[heart tattoo|tattoo]] [[chest tattoo|right on her cleavage]].

For her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this costume, she has her [[medium hair|medium]]-to-[[long hair]] with a dark [[purple hair|purple]] [[streaked hair|streak]] and either her usual [[double-parted bangs|double-parted]] [[crossed bangs]] or [[swept bangs]] [[hair over one eye|covering her left eye]].

title: tim_drake
body:
The third person to become [[Robin (dc)|]]. Tim is different from all the other Robins because he wasn't an orphan, asked to be Robin and wore long pants instead of wearing the famous green short pants that [[Dick Grayson]] and [[Jason Todd]] wore. 

It should be noted that while his parents do die making him an orphan like the others, he didn't start out that way. 

Later Tim adopts the identity of [[Red Robin]] when [[Damian Wayne]] the fifth Robin takes on the role. However, this is short lived thanks to retcons in the DC universe.

Recently, Tim came out as [[Bisexual]] and is currently dating a guy.

title: red_robin
body:
Tim Drake's adopted identity after being the 3rd [[Robin_(dc)|]] before the events of the new 52.

The new 52 timeline in DC saw him revert back to being the 3rd robin along with Damian the 5th robin.

title: neferpitou
body:
Character from [[Hunter x Hunter]], a chimera ant with ant, human and cat genes. Also known as [b]Pitou[/b].

No confirmed gender, although speaks with the male pronoun "boku". Has a prominent bust in both the anime and manga. Furthermore, wears female clothing in the manga and media related to the anime and was VA'd with a feminine voice. Was mistakenly referred to as "male" in an english translation of a official databook, leading to the misconception in the fandom that Pitou is confirmed male.

It can be presumed that the manga version was intended to be female, at least in appearance. As such, can be considered an archetypical catgirl.

Neferpitou's name is a combination of the Egyptian deity Nefertem and a character named Pitou in the French series "Caroline et ses Amis."

Voiced by: [[Fujimura Ayumi]] (Japanese), [[Sarah Anne Williams]] (English)

title: ecole_du_ciel
body:
[b]Mobile Suit Gundam: École du Ciel[/b] (機動戦士ガンダム エコール·デュ·シエル [i]Kidou Senshi Gandamu Ekooru dyu Shieru[/i]) (lit. [b]School Of The Sky[/b]) is a [[Gundam]] manga series written and illustrated by [[Mikimoto Haruhiko]]. It began serialization in 2001 Kadokawa Shoten's [[Gundam Ace]] but has been on hiatus since 2011. Up to 9 volumes were released in English by [[Tokyopop]]. 

In the manga [i]École du Ciel[/i] is the name of an [[Earth Federation]] military school for training future [[mobile suit]] pilots in Montréal, [[Canada]]. Unexpected events occur, exposing cadet Asuna Elmarit and her classmates to the reality that is war.

Ecole du Ciel is a spinoff story set in the Universal Century timeline, taking place before and during the events of [[Zeta Gundam]]. It is one of the few Gundam entries to feature a female protagonist.

title: megidramon
body:
Ultimate-level Evil Dragon-type [[Digimon (creature)|Digimon]], having debuted in [[Digimon Tamers]] in 2001. Megidramon is one of the Four Great Dragons, along with [[Holydramon]], [[Goddramon]] and [[Qinglongmon]]. Of the four, Megidramon is the sole evil member, said to possess the greatest destructive might of the collective as the [[Digital Hazard]] incarnate.

Megidramon is a legless serpent-like [[dragon]] with massive orange batlike [[wings]], [[arm blade|bladed arms]], a long [[tail]] and a huge Digital Hazard mark on its chestplate, now bright red. Its huge maw is lined with [[sharp teeth|sharp]] [[teeth]], its eyes are [[red eyes|red]], and its nasal cavity is implied to be capable of opening up like a secondary mouth.

[u]Common evolutionary throughline:[/u]
[[Jyarimon]] -> [[Gigimon]] -> [[Guilmon]] -> [[Growmon]] -> [[MegaloGrowmon|Megalo Growmon]] -> [b]Megidramon[/b] / [[Dukemon]]
* Megidramon is rumored to be one and the same as [[ChaosDukemon|Chaos Dukemon]].
* Megidramon may evolve further upon acquiring an [[Megidramon X|X-Antibody]].

title: heshikiri_hasebe
body:
A [[Touken Ranbu]] character. 

The personification of the [[katana]] "of the same name":http://meitou.info/index.php/圧切. 

One of [[Oda Nobunaga]]'s favorite swords. His name comes from the incident where a servant angered his owner and hid behind a table to no avail because Oda used Hasebe to slice through the table and kill that servant. Shortly afterwards, he gave the sword to someone who wasn't even one of his trusted people. Because of that incident, Hasebe resents him. 

Hasebe is portrayed as being serious, dutiful and extremely loyal to the Saniwa, to the point that his opening lines are "If it's an order from the Master...". Artists tend to give him a comically serious personality who's utterly obsessed with pleasing the Saniwa (a trait that often comes into play in more comedic side works, such as [i]Hanamaru[/i] or the official Anthalogy; see Pool #11476 for this portrayal). He is also presented as a foil to fellow swords [[Ookurikara]] and [[Shokudaikiri Mitsutada]].

He has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. His standard outfit are purple [[robe]]s, [[white gloves]] and [[sode]] on each shoulder. His casual outfit is a purple and white [[track suit]]. His [[Heshikiri Hasebe (Kiwame)|Kiwame]] form has him dress similarly to a [[priest]], reflecting how his later owner, Kuroda Yoshitaka, converted to Christianity later in life.

He is featured in [i][[Touken Ranbu: Hanamaru]][/i] as one of the major supporting characters, as the [[Saniwa (touken ranbu)|]]'s secretary sword. His loyalty to the Saniwa is more exaggerated in this version. 

h4. See also

* [[Hasebe Shikiri]] (equivalent [[Shinken!!]] character)
